hpnicfLicense.name: hpnicfLicense

revisions.description: Initial version of this MIB module.

hpnicfLicense.description: This MIB is used to manage license, including license key, activation key and activation file.

hpnicfLicenseNotifyEnable.name: hpnicfLicenseNotifyEnable
hpnicfLicenseNotifyEnable.description: This object indicates whether the notifications of license should be generated.

hpnicfLicenseOpEntryMaxNum.name: hpnicfLicenseOpEntryMaxNum
hpnicfLicenseOpEntryMaxNum.description: This object indicates the maximum number of entries that may be held in hpnicfLicenseOpEntry. When the number of entries in hpnicfLicenseOpEntry reached the value of this object, the oldest entry would be destroyed automatic after executing a new operation.

hpnicfLicenseNextFreeOpIndex.name: hpnicfLicenseNextFreeOpIndex
hpnicfLicenseNextFreeOpIndex.description: This object indicates the appropriate value for hpnicfLicenseOpIndex that can be used to create an entry in hpnicfLicenseOpTable.

hpnicfLicenseDevInfoTable.name: hpnicfLicenseDevInfoTable
hpnicfLicenseDevInfoTable.description: A table that displays device information which use to apply license.

hpnicfLicenseDevInfoEntry.name: hpnicfLicenseDevInfoEntry
hpnicfLicenseDevInfoEntry.description: A set of objects that displays device information of license.

hpnicfLicensePhysicalIndex.name: hpnicfLicensePhysicalIndex
hpnicfLicensePhysicalIndex.description: The entPhysicalIndex of the device. The meaning of this object is associated with the management state which from hpnicfLicenseInstallType. Note that: 1) hpnicfLicenseInstallType is installInChassis. This object represents the entPhysicalIndex of the local active MPU. 2) hpnicfLicenseInstallType is installInSlot. This object represents the entPhysicalIndex of MPU boards. 3) hpnicfLicenseInstallType is installInCPU. This object represents the entPhysicalIndex of the CPUs on an MPU board.

hpnicfLicenseSN.name: hpnicfLicenseSN
hpnicfLicenseSN.description: The serial number of the device.

hpnicfLicenseDeviceIDType.name: hpnicfLicenseDeviceIDType
hpnicfLicenseDeviceIDType.description: The types of device ID. invalid - The device ID is invalid. keyString - The device ID is a string. file - The device ID is a file.

hpnicfLicenseDeviceID.name: hpnicfLicenseDeviceID
hpnicfLicenseDeviceID.description: A string represents the device ID. For example: Device ID: XXXX-XXXX-XXXX-XXXX-XXXX-XXXX-XXXX-XXXX This object can not be read when hpnicfLicenseDeviceIDType is invalid, and a file name with full path while hpnicfLicenseDeviceIDType is file. For example: Device ID: flash:/xxx.did

hpnicfLicenseHardwareInfo.name: hpnicfLicenseHardwareInfo
hpnicfLicenseHardwareInfo.description: The information of the device hardware.

hpnicfLicenseMaxNum.name: hpnicfLicenseMaxNum
hpnicfLicenseMaxNum.description: The max number of licenses that can be installed in device.

hpnicfLicenseRecyclableNum.name: hpnicfLicenseRecyclableNum
hpnicfLicenseRecyclableNum.description: The number of recyclable storage for licenses.

hpnicfLicenseInstallType.name: hpnicfLicenseInstallType
hpnicfLicenseInstallType.description: The state of license management. This object determines the instance of hpnicfLicensePhysicalIndex and hpnicfLicenseOpPhysicalIndex. invalid - The state is invalid as driver fault. installInChassis - License is chassis locked. installInSlot - License is MPU locked. installInCPU - License is CPU locked.

hpnicfLicenseFileStoragePath.name: hpnicfLicenseFileStoragePath
hpnicfLicenseFileStoragePath.description: The storage path of the installed license files.

hpnicfLicenseGeneralTable.name: hpnicfLicenseGeneralTable
hpnicfLicenseGeneralTable.description: A table that displays general information of installed license.

hpnicfLicenseGeneralEntry.name: hpnicfLicenseGeneralEntry
hpnicfLicenseGeneralEntry.description: A set of objects that displays general information of installed license.

hpnicfLicenseIndex.name: hpnicfLicenseIndex
hpnicfLicenseIndex.description: ID that can be used to uniquely identify a license. It may use a stable storage index.

hpnicfLicenseFeature.name: hpnicfLicenseFeature
hpnicfLicenseFeature.description: The name of the licensed feature. When there multiple features, this object will display with space as delimiter.

hpnicfLicenseProductDescr.name: hpnicfLicenseProductDescr
hpnicfLicenseProductDescr.description: The product description in a license.

hpnicfLicenseFileDescr.name: hpnicfLicenseFileDescr
hpnicfLicenseFileDescr.description: The file description in activation file.

hpnicfLicenseState.name: hpnicfLicenseState
hpnicfLicenseState.description: The state of an installed license. invalid - The license is invalid and cannot be used. inuse - The license is being used. usable - The license is available for use. 1. If multiple days-restricted licenses for one feature are installed, only one license is in 'inuse' state and the rest licenses are in 'usable' state. 2. A date-restricted license is in this state if its start date is not reached. expired - The license has expired. uninstalled - The license has been uninstalled. unusable - The license cannot be used.

hpnicfLicenseActivationFile.name: hpnicfLicenseActivationFile
hpnicfLicenseActivationFile.description: The name of an installed activation file, with device name and file name. For example: flash:/license/210231A1V0A1290000012013032718261184345.ak

hpnicfLicenseActivationKey.name: hpnicfLicenseActivationKey
hpnicfLicenseActivationKey.description: The activation key that has been installed. For example: Activation Key: dyKT-x3vc-W@Ca-n4gn-Yo83-rVY3-C8:7-e3pg

hpnicfLicenseLicenseKey.name: hpnicfLicenseLicenseKey
hpnicfLicenseLicenseKey.description: The license key that has been installed.

hpnicfLicenseUninstActivationFile.name: hpnicfLicenseUninstActivationFile
hpnicfLicenseUninstActivationFile.description: If an activation file is uninstalled, the system creates an uninstall file. Use this file together with the SN and DID of the transfer destination to register the license for the transfer destination.

hpnicfLicenseUninstActivationKey.name: hpnicfLicenseUninstActivationKey
hpnicfLicenseUninstActivationKey.description: If an activation key is uninstalled, the system creates an uninstall key. Use this key together with the SN and DID of the transfer destination to register the license for the transfer destination.

hpnicfLicenseType.name: hpnicfLicenseType
hpnicfLicenseType.description: License type by validity period. unknown - The system cannot obtain the license type. permanent - Purchased license that never expires and is always valid. daysRestricted - Purchased license that is valid for a period in days. trialDaysRestricted - Free trial license that is valid for a period in days. dateRestricted - Purchased license that is valid for an absolute date range. trialDateRestricted - Free trial license that is valid for an absolute date range. countRestricted - Purchased license that is valid for several useing times. trialCountRestricted - Free trial license that is valid for several useing times.

hpnicfLicenseInstalledTime.name: hpnicfLicenseInstalledTime
hpnicfLicenseInstalledTime.description: Time when the license was installed. For example, it would be displayed as: 2013-9-20,13:30:15.0

hpnicfLicenseUninstalledTime.name: hpnicfLicenseUninstalledTime
hpnicfLicenseUninstalledTime.description: The time when the license was uninstalled. For example, it would be displayed as: 2013-9-26,15:12:20.0

hpnicfLicenseDaysLeft.name: hpnicfLicenseDaysLeft
hpnicfLicenseDaysLeft.description: Remaining days of the license. This object is available for a days-restricted license.

hpnicfLicenseValidityStart.name: hpnicfLicenseValidityStart
hpnicfLicenseValidityStart.description: Start date for a date-restricted license. This object is available for a date-restricted license. But if the start date is not limited, this object is unavailable. For example, it would be displayed as: 2013-9-26,15:12:20.0

hpnicfLicenseValidityEnd.name: hpnicfLicenseValidityEnd
hpnicfLicenseValidityEnd.description: End date for a date-restricted license. This object is available for a date-restricted license. But if the end date is not limited, this object is unavailable. For example, it would be displayed as: 2014-9-26,15:12:20.0

hpnicfLicenseExpiredDays.name: hpnicfLicenseExpiredDays
hpnicfLicenseExpiredDays.description: Passed days after a license has been expired.

hpnicfLicenseCount.name: hpnicfLicenseCount
hpnicfLicenseCount.description: The effective number of license. This object is available for a count-restricted license.

hpnicfLicenseFeatureTable.name: hpnicfLicenseFeatureTable
hpnicfLicenseFeatureTable.description: A table that displays installed licenses for features.

hpnicfLicenseFeatureEntry.name: hpnicfLicenseFeatureEntry
hpnicfLicenseFeatureEntry.description: A set of objects that displays installed licenses for features.

hpnicfLicenseFeatureName.name: hpnicfLicenseFeatureName
hpnicfLicenseFeatureName.description: Feature that must be licensed before being used.

hpnicfLicenseFeatureState.name: hpnicfLicenseFeatureState
hpnicfLicenseFeatureState.description: License type by purchasing state. notLicensed - The feature is not licensed. trialLicense - The feature is using trial license. formalLicense - The feature is using purchased license.

hpnicfLicenseOpTable.name: hpnicfLicenseOpTable
hpnicfLicenseOpTable.description: A table that used to install or uninstall license.

hpnicfLicenseOpEntry.name: hpnicfLicenseOpEntry
hpnicfLicenseOpEntry.description: A set of objects used to install or uninstall license.

hpnicfLicenseOpIndex.name: hpnicfLicenseOpIndex
hpnicfLicenseOpIndex.description: ID that can be used to uniquely identify an operation.

hpnicfLicenseOpPhysicalIndex.name: hpnicfLicenseOpPhysicalIndex
hpnicfLicenseOpPhysicalIndex.description: This object indicates that the entPhysicalIndex of the device where the operation is being executed. The meaning of this object is associated with the management state from hpnicfLicenseInstallType. Note that: 1) hpnicfLicenseInstallType is installInChassis. This object represents the entPhysicalIndex of chassis local master. 2) hpnicfLicenseInstallType is installInSlot. This object represents the entPhysicalIndex of MPU boards. 3) hpnicfLicenseInstallType is installInCPU. This object represents the entPhysicalIndex of CPUs. This object must be set and can not be set to zero when executing an operation.

hpnicfLicenseOpType.name: hpnicfLicenseOpType
hpnicfLicenseOpType.description: The type of this operation. compress - Compress the license storage if the free license storage is not sufficient. Note that: 1) After compressing, the expired licenses and uninstalled licenses in the storage area will be cleared. 2) The DID changes each time the license storage is compressed. 3) Before performing a compression, make sure all activation files generated based on the old DID have been installed. They cannot be installed after the compression. delete - Compress one license storage only. installActivationFile - Install an activation file. installActivationKey - Install an activation key. installLicenseKey - Install a license key. uninstallActivationFile - Uninstall an activation file. uninstallActivationKey - Uninstall an activation key. uninstallLicenseKey - Uninstall a license key.

hpnicfLicenseOpString.name: hpnicfLicenseOpString
hpnicfLicenseOpString.description: This object might be an activation file name, an activation key or a license key that is to be installed, uninstalled or deleted. The operation type is specified in hpnicfLicenseOpType. For compressing, this object must not be bound when creating a row. For deletion, this object could be an activation file, an activation key or a license key. For installActivationFile and uninstallActivationFile, this object must be a name of an activation file, with full path. Such as: flash:/license/210231A1V0A1290000012013032718261184345.ak For installActivationKey and uninstallActivationKey, this object must be an activation key. For installLicenseKey and uninstallLicenseKey, this object must be a license key.

hpnicfLicenseOpNotifyEnable.name: hpnicfLicenseOpNotifyEnable
hpnicfLicenseOpNotifyEnable.description: This object indicates whether 'hpnicfLicenseOpCompletion' notifications will be generated after this operation is completed. Note that, this object is meaningless if the value of 'hpnicfLicenseNotifyEnable' is 'false'.

hpnicfLicenseOpRowStatus.name: hpnicfLicenseOpRowStatus
hpnicfLicenseOpRowStatus.description: The status of this conceptual row. When an entry was in active status, values of any object in this entry are forbidden to be changed.

hpnicfLicenseOpState.name: hpnicfLicenseOpState
hpnicfLicenseOpState.description: The state of this operation. opInProgress - This operation is in progress. opSuccessful - Successful to execute this operation. opFailed - Failed to execute this operation, and 'hpnicfLicenseOpFailedReason' will indicate the detailed cause of the failure.

hpnicfLicenseOpFailedReason.name: hpnicfLicenseOpFailedReason
hpnicfLicenseOpFailedReason.description: This object indicates the detailed cause of the failure when this operation failed.

hpnicfLicenseOpEndTime.name: hpnicfLicenseOpEndTime
hpnicfLicenseOpEndTime.description: The value of sysUpTime when the operation is done.

hpnicfLicenseOpCompletion.name: hpnicfLicenseOpCompletion
hpnicfLicenseOpCompletion.description: This notification is generated when a license operation completed.

hpnicfLicenseActivationFileLost.name: hpnicfLicenseActivationFileLost
hpnicfLicenseActivationFileLost.description: This notification is generated when the activation file has been lost.

hpnicfLicenseActivationFileRestored.name: hpnicfLicenseActivationFileRestored
hpnicfLicenseActivationFileRestored.description: This notification is generated when the activation file restored successfully.

hpnicfLicenseExpired.name: hpnicfLicenseExpired
hpnicfLicenseExpired.description: This notification is generated when the license expires.

hpnicfLicenseExpireWarning.name: hpnicfLicenseExpireWarning
hpnicfLicenseExpireWarning.description: This notification is generated when is about to expire.

hpnicfLicenseBindValidityPeriodRemaining.name: hpnicfLicenseBindValidityPeriodRemaining
hpnicfLicenseBindValidityPeriodRemaining.description: This object indicates the remaining days before the feature's license expires.
